'''Behavioral strategy''' refers to the study of corporate or business strategies from a [[Microfoundations|micro-foundations perspective]]. This area of study is emerging in the field of [[management]] and [[economics]]. It considers the role of conscious and unconscious [[Bias|biases]] of executives, managers, teams, and organizations in strategic [[Decision theory|decision making]]. The field is emerging following similar developments in the fields of [[behavioral economics]] and [[behavioral finance]].

